				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\upmu$$\end{document}W and continues operating up to 500 μ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\upmu$$\end{document}W while maintaining a power efficiency of more than 60%. Compared to the low voltage step-up converter the range is much wider due to the higher overdrive voltage on the converter drivers but has a higher lower limit due to additional parasitic capacitances and smaller flying capacitors.

