As mentioned earlier the reason for having three different converters is to enable a wide input-voltage range. Seen in Fig. 15 is the output voltage and power efficiency for input voltages between 500 mV and 11 V with a target output voltage of 1.8 V and a 200 kΩ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
